0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":29046,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/10\/spouses-kissing-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":34162,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Spouses kissing each other while fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 10, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, leaned forward to kiss me. I said, \u201cI am fasting.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cAnd I am fasting,\u201d then he kissed me. Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 24861 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0649 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3785,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/24\/fasting-bad-behavior-arguments\/","url_meta":{"origin":34162,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: A fasting person must give up bad behavior","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen one of you wakes up in the morning for fasting, then he should not use obscene language or behave foolishly. If anyone abuses him or fights with him, he should say twice: Indeed, I am\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28106,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/23\/allah-has-waived-fasting-half-of-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":34162,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Allah has waived fasting, half of prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 23, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Amr ibn Umayyah reported: I came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, from a journey and he said, \u201cStay to eat, O Abu Umayyah.\u201d I said, \u201cIndeed, I am fasting.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cCome close to me and I will tell you about the traveler.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23295,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/06\/23\/siyam-sawm-lies-obscenity-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":34162,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Siyam: True fasting is from falsehood and sin","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 23, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, fasting is not only from eating and drinking. Rather, fasting is from vanity and obscenity. If someone abuses you or acts foolish against you, then say: Indeed, I am fasting.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 3479\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Ri